# Codex Review Gate (ai-devkit)

After **plan** or **implement**, Cursor MUST request Codex review. Do not mark work complete without review (or documented fallback).

## Workflow

### Plan (multi-file / risky change)

1. Write `.agent/PLAN.md`
2. Run: `bash scripts/request_codex_review.sh --plan`
3. Read `.agent/CODEX_REVIEW.md` — fix plan if `fix-required` before coding

### Implement

1. Implement + verify
2. Write `.agent/CLAUDE_IMPLEMENTATION.md` (status: `ready-for-review`)
3. Run: `bash scripts/request_codex_review.sh`
4. Fix all `critical` and `major` findings; re-run review if substantial

## ai-devkit commands

```bash
ai-devkit agent list --json          # Codex must be running in this repo
bash scripts/request_codex_review.sh --plan
bash scripts/request_codex_review.sh
bash scripts/request_codex_review.sh --send-only   # fire-and-forget
```

Fallback CLI: `npx ai-devkit@latest agent ...` if `ai-devkit` not on PATH.

## If Codex unavailable

1. Note in `.agent/STATUS.md`: "Codex skipped — Cursor self-review"
2. Use skill `betterbox-code-review` → write `.agent/CODEX_REVIEW.md`
3. Retry when Codex is running

## Coordination files

| File | When |
|---|---|
| `.agent/PLAN.md` | Before implement |
| `.agent/CLAUDE_IMPLEMENTATION.md` | After implement |
| `.agent/CODEX_REVIEW.md` | Codex output |
| `.agent/STATUS.md` | After review loop |

Config: `.ai-devkit.json` — skills `agent-communication`, `agent-orchestration`, `dev-review`.
